    "rawText": "We have x1 = 7, x2 = 3, x3 = 1. It is not at all clear what the pattern here is, so we calculate\nthe next few terms:\n                                    23 × 1 − 53   −30\n                               x4 =             =     = −5\n                                     5×1+1         6\n                                    23 × (−5) − 53   −168\n                               x5 =                =      =7\n                                     5 × (−5) + 1     −24\n\nso x6 = 3, x7 = 1, x8 = −5 and so on. Thus the terms repeat in a cycle with length 4, and as\n100 = 25 × 4, we see that x100 = −5, which is option A.\n\n\n\n\nVersion 1.1, March 2019                                                                 Page 14\n\n                                                                                    © UCLES 2019"
